ing of events and feelings. The chapters present each stage of case formulation in depth, followed by case examples that apply the case formulation method to a cross-section of clinical disorders, including depression, anxiety, trauma, and eating disorders"--Publicity materials. (PsycINFO Database Record (c) 2014 APA, all rights reserved).  aElectronic reproduction.bWashington, D.C. :cAmerican Psychological Association,d2014.nAvailable via World Wide Web.nAccess limited by licensing agreement.7s2014    dcunns  a21 44 57 2aEmotions. 2aPsychotherapyxmethods. 2aNarration. 2aPatient Care Planning. 0aEmotions. 0aPsychotherapyxMethodology. 0aNarration (Rhetoric) 0aMedical protocols.1 aGreenberg, Leslie S.2 aAmerican Psychological Association.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://ovidsp.ovid.com/ovidweb.cgi?T=JS&NEWS=N&PAGE=toc&SEARCH=2014-25807.dd&LINKTYPE=asBody&D=psbk403MacEwan University Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/direct.asp?db=pzh&jid=%22201425807%22&scope=site403Concordia University of Edmonton Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&db=pzh&jid=201425807&site=ehost-live  hUAINzPSYCBOOKS  hUAINmCONCORDIAzPSYCBKSCON  hUAINmGR_MAC_INTzPSYCBKSGM  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6749848-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu12/2/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBOOKS  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6749848-2001lINTERNETmCONCORDIArYsYtE-RESOURCEu12/2/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSCON  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6749848-3001lINTERNETmGR_MAC_INTrYsYtE-RESOURCEu12/2/2014xE-BOOKzPSYCBKSGM01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n82120862bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/311113936